name: Governor David Ige
tweet: Dawn and I got the opportunity to thank airport screeners who have been helping screen incoming passengers since 2020. I know it’s been an oftentimes thankless job, but we are grateful for their dedication to helping ensure we kept our community as safe and healthy as possible.  https://t.co/NIgHpodXmn

name: Governor David Ige
tweet: In my State of the State, I also discussed rethinking a regional library like Pearl City, to begin to offer even more expansive services to help the community.   To read more:  https://t.co/G30snyfPig To subscribe to the CC newsletter:  https://t.co/IDaQ2rBtt4

name: Governor David Ige
tweet: Libraries can be the great equalizer, and they’re brimming with resources. Not only are books available, but the Hawaiʻi State Public Library also offers free online courses and programs that can help beef up your computer and internet skills.

name: Governor David Ige
tweet: There are countless stories of how libraries have helped people throughout the years. In Maui, a man escaped homelessness after writing a novel on a library computer. Librarians have also heard stories of how kids began their love of reading through story time.

name: Governor David Ige
tweet: Here's just a quick snapshot of the work these Guardsmembers did during the last few years. A total of 1,894 people helped support this mission.  https://t.co/omEqUpCO0v

name: Governor David Ige
tweet: The Hawaiʻi National Guard continues to live up to its motto “always ready and always there.”  They’ve demonstrated this throughout the pandemic, and during times of state crises and natural disasters throughout the last several decades. We are grateful for your service.  https://t.co/fNVCTUlB3Q

name: Governor David Ige
tweet: After more than two years, the Hawaiʻi National Guard is ramping down its mission to help the state with its COVID-19 response. During their mission, Guardsmen helped with airport temperature screenings, testing, mapping COVID exposures, and more.  https://t.co/u5ywfxJV37

name: Governor David Ige
tweet: Oil companies raised their prices in recent weeks impacting wallets nationwide. It's one reason Hawaii is focused on transitioning to renewable energy. Kauai is a great example. 70% of their electricity grid is powered by renewables, better insulating them from oil market prices.
